[thinking] **Considering test environments**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m reflecting on POM lists and whether testcontainers should be optional without scope, but it seems it doesn't apply to Gradle since Maven treats optional dependencies differently. I wonder about the transitive nature of test dependencies. For generated tests, using a public API in-memory reduces complexity, but connecting to Neo4j requires a Docker image. I need to sort out the issue with the Java run failing on updates, plus existing failures with object mapping could indicate deeper setup problems. I should definitely research documentation further.
[thinking] 
